{
  "abstract": "Over three billion people are currently malnourished due to nutritional\r\ndeficiencies (eg, iron, zinc, vitamin A), resulting in learning disabilities\r\namong children, increased morbidity and mortality rates, lower\r\nworker productivity, and high healthcare costs.\r\n• Most staple food crops can be enriched (biofortified) with\r\nmicronutrients using crop improvement tools.\r\n• Access to plant genetic resources is essential for crop improvement.\r\n• Globally, over 7.4 million accessions of economically important\r\nspecies are conserved in 1,750 genebanks (about 0.74 million in 11\r\nCGIAR genebanks).......",
